			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">It would be useful to have Python bindings for NaCl's IMC interface
(i.e. imc_sendmsg(), imc_recvmsg() etc.).

There are two cases for this:

 * in trusted code
 * in untrusted code

For trusted code, the Python wrappers would have to use the NaClDesc
interface.

For untrusted code, the Python wrappers could either use the imc_*
syscalls directly, or they could also use the NaClDesc interface.
(Currently NaClDesc does not work in untrusted code but it could be
extended to support this.)

The use case I currently have in mind for this is implementing the
trusted side of POSIX-over-IMC in Python.
